@page "/js-alert"
@inject IJSRuntime JS

<h3>.NET → JavaScript Interop (Alert)</h3>

<button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="ShowAlert">
    Show Alert
</button>

@code {
    private async Task ShowAlert()
    {
        //Calling JavaScript from .NET
        await JS.InvokeVoidAsync(
            "alert",
            "Hello from Blazor (.NET 10)"
        );
    }
}
How This Works (Line by Line)
1. Injecting IJSRuntime
IJSRuntime is the interop gateway

It allows Blazor to execute JavaScript in the browser
2. User Action Triggers JS Call(Clicking Button)
JS interop is triggered only after rendering

Avoid calling JS during initialization or prerendering
3. Calling JavaScript from .NET